                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221 Dahl, Harold/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vigo</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Graves</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vigo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-27T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 27, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 30, 5 p.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d541fn6">Not printed; it instructed the
                        Consul not to attend the court martial of Harold Dahl (852.2221 Dahl,
                        Harold/15).</note> I am informed from Salamanca that Harold Dahl is to be
                    tried by court martial at 11:00 o’clock on the morning of October 5. The
                    assistant judge in charge of the case, who was apparently the person telephoning
                    me, asked that I attend the trial. <pb facs="0564" n="552" xml:id="pg_552"/> He
                    appeared particularly interested due to the foreign correspondents at Salamanca
                    who will cover the case. I told him, however, that I was not planning to attend
                    the trial. Repeated to Seville.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Graves</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
